<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 2em;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }
        .csp-info {
            background: #fff3cd;
            border: 1px solid #ffeaa7;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .csp-policy {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border-left: 4px solid #007bff;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            font-family: monospace;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
        }
        .test-section {
            background: #e7f3ff;
            border: 1px solid #b3d9ff;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .warning {
            background: #f8d7da;
            border: 1px solid #f5c6cb;
            color: #721c24;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        /* This should work with strict CSP */
        .safe-style {
            color: #28a745;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1><%= title %></h1>

    <div class="csp-info">
        <h2>Content Security Policy</h2>
        <p>This page implements a strict CSP policy to test security headers:</p>
        <div class="csp-policy"><%= csp %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="test-section">
        <h2>CSP Tests</h2>
        <p class="safe-style">✓ This text uses safe inline styles that should work with CSP</p>

        <script>
            // This inline script should work because we allow 'unsafe-inline' for scripts
            console.log('CSP Test: Inline script executed successfully');
            document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
                const testResults = document.getElementById('csp-test-results');
                testResults.innerHTML = '<span class="safe-style">✓ JavaScript execution successful</span>';
            });
        </script>

        <div id="csp-test-results">Testing JavaScript...</div>

        <h3>Security Headers Present:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><code>Content-Security-Policy</code></li>
            <li><code>X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff</code></li>
            <li><code>X-Frame-Options: DENY</code></li>
            <li><code>X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block</code></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="test-section">
        <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
        <p>Use this page to test that Printeer properly handles pages with strict Content Security Policy headers.</p>
        <p>The CSP should not interfere with PDF generation while still providing security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="warning">
        <h3>⚠️ CSP Violations</h3>
        <p>Check the browser console for any CSP violations. In a strict CSP environment, any violations should be logged but not block PDF generation.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>